00:05:03.502 --> 00:05:05.960
And so as we work together with
our product and engineering

00:05:05.960 --> 00:05:10.220
partners, we really wanted to
set out very specific product

00:05:10.220 --> 00:05:13.870
goals and redefine how we're
positioning Play, things

00:05:13.870 --> 00:05:16.510
like telling a cohesive
brand story among all

00:05:16.510 --> 00:05:18.530
the different content types.

00:05:18.530 --> 00:05:20.890
We want to create a
consistent and responsive UX

00:05:20.890 --> 00:05:23.120
framework that can scale.

00:05:23.120 --> 00:05:25.641
We wanted to build shared
engineering components,

00:05:25.641 --> 00:05:27.390
and we wanted to make
sure we were working

00:05:27.390 --> 00:05:32.110
with a top down product vision
that everyone could align to.

00:05:32.110 --> 00:05:34.630
Maybe most importantly,
the design team really

00:05:34.630 --> 00:05:36.850
wanted to focus on
building relationships

00:05:36.850 --> 00:05:39.720
with partners outside of design.

00:05:39.720 --> 00:05:42.150
Our engineering partners,
our product partners,

00:05:42.150 --> 00:05:45.980
our marketing partners
with very early involvement

00:05:45.980 --> 00:05:48.920
in an iterative design approach.

00:05:48.920 --> 00:05:51.190
And so we set out to define
a visual and interaction

00:05:51.190 --> 00:05:54.670
framework that can scale
responsibly to multiple device

00:05:54.670 --> 00:05:56.780
types and orientations.

00:05:56.780 --> 00:05:59.130
We want it to be very
expressive with our color

00:05:59.130 --> 00:06:00.810
to give each product
in the family

00:06:00.810 --> 00:06:04.650
its own personality while
not overwhelming the content.

00:06:04.650 --> 00:06:07.130
And also because Play
is a media product,

00:06:07.130 --> 00:06:10.000
we wanted to make sure that our
content is front and center.

00:06:10.000 --> 00:06:13.350
We wanted to represent
it as best as we could.

00:06:13.350 --> 00:06:16.200
And so as we were thinking
about our current design

00:06:16.200 --> 00:06:18.460
in the material
world, the challenge

00:06:18.460 --> 00:06:19.972
seemed daunting at first.

00:06:19.972 --> 00:06:21.680
You know, you have a
new platform update,

00:06:21.680 --> 00:06:22.860
things can be a little scary.

00:06:22.860 --> 00:06:23.776
What am I going to do?

00:06:23.776 --> 00:06:25.820
Do we redesign
from the ground up?

00:06:25.820 --> 00:06:29.100
And I'm sure a lot of you guys
are probably in the same boat.

00:06:29.100 --> 00:06:32.520
And so, you've recently
updated your products.

00:06:32.520 --> 00:06:35.920
How should you go about
addressing this issue.

00:06:35.920 --> 00:06:39.410
And we cose to see it rather as
a challenge, as an opportunity.

00:06:39.410 --> 00:06:44.180
So we wanted to take a step
back and address and identify

00:06:44.180 --> 00:06:46.710
some of these core
opportunities in our UI.

00:06:46.710 --> 00:06:48.950
And so we started with
our current product.

00:06:48.950 --> 00:06:51.880
We wanted to identify
our hero screens,

00:06:51.880 --> 00:06:53.620
and review them
together as a team.

00:06:53.620 --> 00:06:56.210
And so our hero screens
were the key screens

00:06:56.210 --> 00:07:00.190
that represented a subset of
the pages within the entire UI.

00:07:00.190 --> 00:07:02.370
Things like our
product detail pages,

00:07:02.370 --> 00:07:05.750
our library views,
our landing pages.

00:07:05.750 --> 00:07:09.090
And we wanted to identify the
common UI elements and patterns

00:07:09.090 --> 00:07:12.830
that existed across these
pages, and take note of them

00:07:12.830 --> 00:07:15.520
and look at where we
could make improvements.

00:07:15.520 --> 00:07:17.310
And because design
doesn't happen

00:07:17.310 --> 00:07:20.500
in a vacuum and
great product doesn't

00:07:20.500 --> 00:07:24.610
get created without advocacy
of folks outside of design,

00:07:24.610 --> 00:07:26.370
things like quality
and craftsmanship,

00:07:26.370 --> 00:07:28.090
and attention to detail.

00:07:28.090 --> 00:07:30.110
It's very important for
groups outside of design

00:07:30.110 --> 00:07:33.570
to understand these things
and to embrace them.

00:07:33.570 --> 00:07:35.490
And so we really wanted
to workshop together

00:07:35.490 --> 00:07:36.920
with these partners.

00:07:36.920 --> 00:07:40.770
Inviting them in, doing a
series of different workshops,

00:07:40.770 --> 00:07:44.090
getting their feedback and
involvement as early and often

00:07:44.090 --> 00:07:46.890
as possible so that we
could all be thinking ahead

00:07:46.890 --> 00:07:49.540
and understand the vision
that we're sharing together.

00:07:49.540 --> 00:07:53.170
And so workshopping helps get
everybody on the same page

00:07:53.170 --> 00:07:55.590
and gets a lot of
high-level thinking there.

00:07:55.590 --> 00:07:58.040
But our next step
was to really get

00:07:58.040 --> 00:07:59.900
a little more tactical about it.

00:07:59.900 --> 00:08:02.690
Meaning like our team
likes to use Sprint

00:08:02.690 --> 00:08:05.750
methods, where we take very
specific design challenges

00:08:05.750 --> 00:08:08.760
and go heads down
across disciplines,

00:08:08.760 --> 00:08:11.390
working on very similar
design problems.

00:08:11.390 --> 00:08:13.290
Again sharing that work often.

00:08:13.290 --> 00:08:15.190
And this can be a
day-long exercise,

00:08:15.190 --> 00:08:16.980
this can be a
week-long exercise.

00:08:16.980 --> 00:08:20.280
It just depends on the
complexity of the problem.

00:08:20.280 --> 00:08:22.500
And so quickly recap here.

00:08:22.500 --> 00:08:26.184
I just want underscore the
fact that it's really important

00:08:26.184 --> 00:08:27.850
to approach material
design and thinking

00:08:27.850 --> 00:08:30.480
about the opportunities
within your product.

00:08:30.480 --> 00:08:32.549
It's not just about
design, but it's

00:08:32.549 --> 00:08:34.929
about how you work
together with your teams.

00:08:34.929 --> 00:08:38.039
To bring that institutional
advocacy and importance

00:08:38.039 --> 00:08:42.610
to these sometimes subtle
things., the craftsmanship.

00:08:42.610 --> 00:08:45.100
Thoughtful design is just not
about being a differentiator

00:08:45.100 --> 00:08:45.960
anymore.

00:08:45.960 --> 00:08:50.720
It's pretty much table
stakes at this point.

